==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*xruso-'' ‘ground, ice’.  Apparently there is a cognate in Old High German [[hroso]], [[hrosa]] ‘ice, crust’.  The Germanic root may be from the same Indo-European source as Latin [[crusta]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'hɹu:ze/

===Noun===
'''hrūse''' ''f''
# [[earth]], the [[ground]]

